===Etymology===
From the [[Russian]] ''[[ер]]'' [yer] or ''[[ерь]]'' [yer’]. 

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

#{{Linguistics}} Ultra-short or reduced vowel in Proto- and Late [[Common Slavonic]] (or Slavic), then represented as '''ъ''' (back jer [ŭ]) or '''ь''' (front jer [ĭ]).

